#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:8
msgid "Installation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:9
msgid ""
"Tornado now depends on the `backports.ssl_match_hostname "
"<https://pypi.python.org/pypi/backports.ssl_match_hostname>`_ when "
"running on Python 2.  This will be installed automatically when using "
"``pip`` or ``easy_install``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:13
msgid ""
"Tornado now includes an optional C extension module, which greatly "
"improves performance of websockets.  This extension will be built "
"automatically if a C compiler is found at install time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:18
msgid "New modules"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:20
msgid ""
"The `tornado.platform.asyncio` module provides integration with the "
"``asyncio`` module introduced in Python 3.4 (also available for Python "
"3.3 with ``pip install asyncio``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:25
msgid "`tornado.auth`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:27
msgid ""
"Added `.GoogleOAuth2Mixin` support authentication to Google services with"
" OAuth 2 instead of OpenID and OAuth 1."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:29
msgid ""
"`.FacebookGraphMixin` has been updated to use the current Facebook login "
"URL, which saves a redirect."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:33
msgid "`tornado.concurrent`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:35
msgid ""
"``TracebackFuture`` now accepts a ``timeout`` keyword argument (although "
"it is still incorrect to use a non-zero timeout in non-blocking code)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:39
msgid "``tornado.curl_httpclient``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:41
msgid ""
"``tornado.curl_httpclient`` now works on Python 3 with the soon-to-be-"
"released pycurl 7.19.3, which will officially support Python 3 for the "
"first time.  Note that there are some unofficial Python 3 ports of pycurl"
" (Ubuntu has included one for its past several releases); these are not "
"supported for use with Tornado."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:48
msgid "`tornado.escape`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:50
msgid "`.xhtml_escape` now escapes apostrophes as well."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:51
msgid ""
"`tornado.escape.utf8`, `.to_unicode`, and `.native_str` now raise "
"`TypeError` instead of `AssertionError` when given an invalid value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:55
msgid "`tornado.gen`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:57
msgid ""
"Coroutines may now yield dicts in addition to lists to wait for multiple "
"tasks in parallel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:59
msgid ""
"Improved performance of `tornado.gen` when yielding a `.Future` that is "
"already done."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:63
msgid "`tornado.httpclient`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:65
msgid ""
"`tornado.httpclient.HTTPRequest` now uses property setters so that "
"setting attributes after construction applies the same conversions as "
"``__init__`` (e.g. converting the body attribute to bytes)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:70
msgid "`tornado.httpserver`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:72
msgid ""
"Malformed ``x-www-form-urlencoded`` request bodies will now log a warning"
" and continue instead of causing the request to fail (similar to the "
"existing handling of malformed ``multipart/form-data`` bodies.  This is "
"done mainly because some libraries send this content type by default even"
" when the data is not form-encoded."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:77
msgid "Fix some error messages for unix sockets (and other non-IP sockets)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:80
msgid "`tornado.ioloop`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:82
msgid ""
"`.IOLoop` now uses `~.IOLoop.handle_callback_exception` consistently for "
"error logging."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:84
msgid ""
"`.IOLoop` now frees callback objects earlier, reducing memory usage while"
" idle."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:86
msgid ""
"`.IOLoop` will no longer call `logging.basicConfig` if there is a handler"
" defined for the root logger or for the ``tornado`` or "
"``tornado.application`` loggers (previously it only looked at the root "
"logger)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:91
msgid "`tornado.iostream`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:93
msgid ""
"`.IOStream` now recognizes ``ECONNABORTED`` error codes in more places "
"(which was mainly an issue on Windows)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:95
msgid ""
"`.IOStream` now frees memory earlier if a connection is closed while "
"there is data in the write buffer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:97
msgid "`.PipeIOStream` now handles ``EAGAIN`` error codes correctly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:98
msgid ""
"`.SSLIOStream` now initiates the SSL handshake automatically without "
"waiting for the application to try and read or write to the connection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:100
msgid ""
"Swallow a spurious exception from ``set_nodelay`` when a connection has "
"been reset."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:104
msgid "`tornado.locale`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:106
msgid ""
"`.Locale.format_date` no longer forces the use of absolute dates in "
"Russian."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:110
msgid "`tornado.log`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:112
msgid ""
"Fix an error from `tornado.log.enable_pretty_logging` when `sys.stderr` "
"does not have an ``isatty`` method."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:114
msgid ""
"`tornado.log.LogFormatter` now accepts keyword arguments ``fmt`` and "
"``datefmt``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:118
msgid "`tornado.netutil`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:120
msgid ""
"`.is_valid_ip` (and therefore ``HTTPRequest.remote_ip``) now rejects "
"empty strings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:122
msgid ""
"Synchronously using `.ThreadedResolver` at import time to resolve a "
"unicode hostname no longer deadlocks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:126
msgid "`tornado.platform.twisted`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:128
msgid "`.TwistedResolver` now has better error handling."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:131
msgid "`tornado.process`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:133
msgid ""
"`.Subprocess` no longer leaks file descriptors if `subprocess.Popen` "
"fails."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:136
msgid "``tornado.simple_httpclient``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:138
msgid ""
"``simple_httpclient`` now applies the ``connect_timeout`` to requests "
"that are queued and have not yet started."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:140
msgid "On Python 2.6, ``simple_httpclient`` now uses TLSv1 instead of SSLv3."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:141
msgid ""
"``simple_httpclient`` now enforces the connect timeout during DNS "
"resolution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:142
msgid ""
"The embedded ``ca-certificates.crt`` file has been updated with the "
"current Mozilla CA list."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:146
msgid "`tornado.web`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:148
msgid ""
"`.StaticFileHandler` no longer fails if the client requests a ``Range`` "
"that is larger than the entire file (Facebook has a crawler that does "
"this)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:150
msgid ""
"`.RequestHandler.on_connection_close` now works correctly on subsequent "
"requests of a keep-alive connection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:152
msgid ""
"New application setting ``default_handler_class`` can be used to easily "
"set up custom 404 pages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:154
msgid ""
"New application settings ``autoreload``, ``compiled_template_cache``, "
"``static_hash_cache``, and ``serve_traceback`` can be used to control "
"individual aspects of debug mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:157
msgid ""
"New methods `.RequestHandler.get_query_argument` and "
"`.RequestHandler.get_body_argument` and new attributes "
"``HTTPRequest.query_arguments`` and ``HTTPRequest.body_arguments`` allow "
"access to arguments without intermingling those from the query string "
"with those from the request body."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:162
msgid ""
"`.RequestHandler.decode_argument` and related methods now raise an "
"``HTTPError(400)`` instead of `UnicodeDecodeError` when the argument "
"could not be decoded."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:165
msgid ""
"`.RequestHandler.clear_all_cookies` now accepts ``domain`` and ``path`` "
"arguments, just like `~.RequestHandler.clear_cookie`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:167
msgid ""
"It is now possible to specify handlers by name when using the `.URLSpec` "
"class."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:169
msgid ""
"`.Application` now accepts 4-tuples to specify the ``name`` parameter "
"(which previously required constructing a `.URLSpec` object instead of a "
"tuple)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:172
msgid ""
"Fixed an incorrect error message when handler methods return a value "
"other than None or a Future."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:174
msgid ""
"Exceptions will no longer be logged twice when using both "
"``@asynchronous`` and ``@gen.coroutine``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:179
msgid "`tornado.websocket`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:181
msgid ""
"`.WebSocketHandler.write_message` now raises `.WebSocketClosedError` "
"instead of `AttributeError` when the connection has been closed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:183
msgid "`.websocket_connect` now accepts preconstructed ``HTTPRequest`` objects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:184
msgid ""
"Fix a bug with `.WebSocketHandler` when used with some proxies that "
"unconditionally modify the ``Connection`` header."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:186
msgid ""
"`.websocket_connect` now returns an error immediately for refused "
"connections instead of waiting for the timeout."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:188
msgid "`.WebSocketClientConnection` now has a ``close`` method."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:191
msgid "`tornado.wsgi`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.2.0.rst:193
msgid ""
"`.WSGIContainer` now calls the iterable's ``close()`` method even if an "
"error is raised, in compliance with the spec."
msgstr ""

